---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout
	title="How to Vote"
	description="Learn when, where, and how to vote in the 2026 UOSU Presidential Election. Voting is March 2–6."
>
	<section class="vote-page">
		<div class="vote-header">
			<h1>How to Vote</h1>
			<p class="vote-lead">
				Voting is open <strong>March 2–6, 2026</strong>. There are three
				ways to cast your ballot — pick whichever is most convenient for
				you.
			</p>
		</div>

		<!-- Voting methods -->
		<div class="methods-grid">
			<article class="method-card">
				<span class="method-icon" aria-hidden="true">🖥️</span>
				<h2>Online</h2>
				<p>
					A secure voting portal will be available on the UOSU website
					starting March 2nd. Log in with your
					<strong>uOttawa Microsoft account</strong> to be redirected to
					your ballot.
				</p>
				<p class="method-note">
					This portal was built by Daniel when he was UOSU
					Communications Commissioner in 2024 and has been used for
					multiple elections since — it's tried and tested.
				</p>
			</article>

			<article class="method-card">
				<span class="method-icon" aria-hidden="true">📧</span>
				<h2>Email</h2>
				<p>
					You will receive an email with a unique ballot link on
					<strong>March 2nd</strong>. Check your
					<strong>uOttawa student email</strong> — and your spam/junk
					folder.
				</p>
				<p class="method-note">
					The email will come from the election provider. If you don't
					see it by end of day March 2nd, check your spam folder or
					contact the Chief Electoral Officer.
				</p>
			</article>

			<article class="method-card">
				<span class="method-icon" aria-hidden="true">🏢</span>
				<h2>In-Person</h2>
				<p>
					Vote in front of the <strong>UOSU office</strong>. Bring your
					<strong>student ID</strong>.
				</p>
				<p class="method-note">
					Specific hours will be announced closer to election day.
					Follow
					<a
						href="https://instagram.com/daniel.thorp.seuo.uosu"
						rel="noopener noreferrer">@daniel.thorp.seuo.uosu</a
					> for updates.
				</p>
			</article>
		</div>

		<!-- Who can vote -->
		<div class="info-section">
			<h2>Who Can Vote?</h2>
			<p>
				All undergraduate students at the University of Ottawa who are
				members of the UOSU are eligible to vote in the presidential
				election.
			</p>
		</div>

		<!-- Important dates -->
		<div class="info-section">
			<h2>Important Dates</h2>
			<ul class="dates-list">
				<li>
					<strong>March 2</strong> — Voting opens (online portal + email
					ballots sent)
				</li>
				<li><strong>March 2–6</strong> — Voting period</li>
				<li><strong>March 6</strong> — Last day to vote</li>
			</ul>
		</div>

		<!-- CTA -->
		<div class="vote-cta">
			<p>Have questions about voting?</p>
			<a href="/get-involved/" class="btn btn-primary">Get in Touch →</a>
		</div>
	</section>
</Layout>

<style>
	.vote-page {
		max-width: var(--content-max);
		margin: 0 auto;
		padding: var(--space-8) var(--space-5) var(--space-9);
	}

	.vote-header {
		margin-bottom: var(--space-8);
	}

	.vote-header h1 {
		margin-bottom: var(--space-3);
	}

	.vote-lead {
		font-size: 1.125rem;
		color: var(--color-muted);
		max-width: 56ch;
		line-height: 1.6;
	}

	/* ── Methods grid ── */
	.methods-grid {
		display: grid;
		grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(min(100%, 280px), 1fr));
		gap: var(--space-5);
		margin-bottom: var(--space-8);
	}

	.method-card {
		padding: var(--space-5);
		background: var(--color-surface);
		border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
		border-radius: var(--radius-2);
		transition: border-color var(--dur-2) var(--ease-out);
	}

	.method-card:hover {
		border-color: var(--color-accent);
	}

	.method-icon {
		font-size: 2rem;
		display: block;
		margin-bottom: var(--space-3);
	}

	.method-card h2 {
		font-size: 1.25rem;
		margin-bottom: var(--space-3);
	}

	.method-card p {
		font-size: 0.9375rem;
		color: var(--color-muted);
		line-height: 1.65;
		margin-bottom: var(--space-3);
	}

	.method-card p:last-child {
		margin-bottom: 0;
	}

	.method-note {
		font-size: 0.875rem !important;
		opacity: 0.8;
	}

	/* ── Info sections ── */
	.info-section {
		margin-bottom: var(--space-7);
		padding-bottom: var(--space-7);
		border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border);
	}

	.info-section:last-of-type {
		border-bottom: none;
	}

	.info-section h2 {
		font-size: 1.5rem;
		margin-bottom: var(--space-4);
	}

	.info-section p {
		font-size: 1rem;
		color: var(--color-muted);
		line-height: 1.65;
		max-width: 60ch;
	}

	.dates-list {
		list-style: none;
		padding: 0;
		display: flex;
		flex-direction: column;
		gap: var(--space-3);
	}

	.dates-list li {
		font-size: 1rem;
		line-height: 1.65;
		padding-left: var(--space-5);
		position: relative;
	}

	.dates-list li::before {
		content: "📅";
		position: absolute;
		left: 0;
	}

	/* ── CTA ── */
	.vote-cta {
		text-align: center;
		padding-top: var(--space-6);
	}

	.vote-cta p {
		color: var(--color-muted);
		margin: 0 auto var(--space-4);
	}

	.btn {
		display: inline-flex;
		align-items: center;
		padding: var(--space-3) var(--space-5);
		font-size: 0.9375rem;
		font-weight: 600;
		border-radius: var(--radius-1);
		text-decoration: none;
		transition:
			background var(--dur-fast) var(--ease-out),
			color var(--dur-fast) var(--ease-out);
	}

	.btn:hover {
		text-decoration: none;
	}

	.btn-primary {
		background: var(--color-accent);
		color: #fff;
	}

	.btn-primary:hover {
		background: var(--color-accent-hover);
		color: #fff;
	}

	@media (max-width: 640px) {
		.vote-page {
			padding: var(--space-6) var(--space-4) var(--space-7);
		}
	}
</style>
